title: Jake Harty
summary: Jake Paul Harty (born January 2, 1991) is a professional Canadian football wide receiver for the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League (CFL). He is a Grey Cup champion after winning with the Ottawa Redblacks in 2016 and he is a Vanier Cup champion as a coach after the Calgary Dinos won the 55th Vanier Cup in 2019.
